## Step 2
The probability $P(|Y/n - 0.25| < 0.05)$ can be interpreted as the probability that the sample proportion $Y/n$ is within 0.05 of the true proportion $p = 0.25$. This is a problem about the concentration of the sample proportion around the population proportion.

