To find $P(52.761 \leq \bar{X} \leq 54.453)$, we need to convert $52.761$ and $54.453$ into z-scores using the formula $z = \frac{\bar{X} - \mu}{\sigma_{\bar{X}}}$. For $\bar{X} = 52.761$, $z = \frac{52.761 - 54.030}{0.846} \approx \frac{-1.269}{0.846} \approx -1.50$. For $\bar{X} = 54.453$, $z = \frac{54.453 - 54.030}{0.846} \approx \frac{0.423}{0.846} \approx 0.50$.

