## Step 2: Recall the formula for the probability of the union of two events
The formula for the probability of the union of two events A and B is given by $P(A \cup B) = P(A) + P(B) - P(A \cap B)$.

## Step 3: Apply the formula to find $P(A \cap B)$
We can rearrange the formula to solve for $P(A \cap B)$: $P(A \cap B) = P(A) + P(B) - P(A \cup B)$. Substituting the given values, we get $P(A \cap B) = 0.8 + 0.5 - 0.9$.

## Step 4: Perform the arithmetic calculation
$P(A \cap B) = 0.8 + 0.5 - 0.9 = 1.3 - 0.9 = 0.4$.

