## Step 3
We are also given that 8% visit neither. This implies that the probability of visiting at least one of them is 1 - 0.08 = 0.92. So, P(PT $\cup$ C) = 0.92.

## Step 4
Using the formula for the union of two events, P(PT $\cup$ C) = P(PT) + P(C) - P(PT $\cap$ C), we can substitute the given values to get 0.92 = P(PT) + P(C) - 0.28.

## Step 5
Simplifying the equation from step 4, we have 0.92 + 0.28 = P(PT) + P(C), which gives 1.2 = P(PT) + P(C).

## Step 6
We are told that the probability of visiting a physical therapist exceeds the probability of visiting a chiropractor by 16%, so P(PT) = P(C) + 0.16.

## Step 7
Substituting P(PT) from step 6 into the equation from step 5, we get 1.2 = (P(C) + 0.16) + P(C).

## Step 8
